---
title: Italian Sausage and Veggie Skewers over Cheesy Herbed Orzo
description: Grilling season is officially here! And what better way to salute outdoor eating than with skewers loaded up with hunks of brightly colored veggies and sausage? In this recipe, they get beautifully charred and smoky over the flames, then are served atop a cheesy and tomato-y orzo pasta. If you’d rather keep things strictly indoors, there’s no need to fret—you can stick those sticks under the broiler for a result that’s just as tasty.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/italian-sausage-and-veggie-skewers-5f31296e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/italian-sausage-and-veggie-skewers-fea6a93f.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/italian-sausage-and-veggie-skewers-58f9355bc9fd083562090d62
cuisine: North America
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 870 kcal
  fat: 43 g
  saturated fat: 20 g
  carbohydrates: 89 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 1030 mg
time required: 25 minutes
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler or #grill{} to high. Place
@wooden skewers{2} in a wide #bowl{}, cover with water, and let soak.

Mince @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Halve and peel @red onion{1/2}(halved and
peeled), then cut each half into four quarters. Slice @yellow squash{1}(sliced
into ½-inch-thick rounds) crosswise into ½-inch-thick rounds. Halve
@grape tomatoes{2%oz}(halved). Halve @lemon{1/2}(halved), then cut one half into
wedges.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add tomatoes and garlic. Cook, stirring, until softened, about
~{2%minutes}. Add @orzo pasta{3%oz} and toss for ~{1%minute}. Pour in 2 1/4
cups water and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then lower heat to medium.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until orzo is al dente, about ~{10%minutes}.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss squash, @Mediterranean spice blend{1%tablespoon},
a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}. Slice
@sweet Italian pork sausage{8%oz} into ½-inch-thick rounds. Remove skewers from
water. Thread squash, sausage, and onion onto skewers, alternating between each.

Place skewers on a #baking sheet{}. Broil until everything is lightly charred
and veggies are tender, about ~{5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If grilling, place skewers on grates directly over flame and cook 5
> minutes per side.

Roughly chop @parsley{2%oz}(roughly chopped), then stir into orzo along with
@Italian cheese blend{1%cup}(adding cheese), allowing cheese to melt. Season
with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and a squeeze of lemon.

Divide orzo between plates, then top with skewers. Serve with lemon wedges on
the side for squeezing over.